          "description": "Total Health & Wellness Medical Center seems like a thoughtful and reliable place for patients seeking quality care. The name itself reflects a strong focus on overall wellbeing, which is always encouraging to see.\n\nJust a small suggestion \u2014 I tried visiting your website to learn more, but it didn\u2019t seem to load. A working, user-friendly website can really help people find important info like services, timings, or how to book appointments.\n\nAs a web developer, I\u2019d be happy to offer help if you ever consider setting up or updating your site. A simple and mobile-friendly presence could really support your outreach. Keep up the great work!",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2pGNVVGTTFVMmhNYzNkaU5ERmZkSGQ2ZFdJdGJtYxAB!2m1!1s0x0:0x3dd458fd0b92ee0e!3m1!1s2@1:CAIQACodChtycF9oOjF5UFM1U2hMc3diNDFfdHd6dWItbmc%7C%7C?hl=en",
          "date": "10 months ago",
          "date_iso8601": "2025-07-31T16:07:31+00:00"
        },
        {
          "username": "Nathaniel Rahav",
          "rating": 1,
          "contributor_id": "113921535184400594140",
          "user_review_count": 3,
          "user_photo_count": 0,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKThZ_bZUmdq4ieRSq1DKkf9rV8SIuwfRSNwkZqdgFibuHn_w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100",
          "description": "I called and asked for a COVID PCR test. The man who answered the phone told me it cost $295 and would be performed by a mobile tester who could come to my car in midtown south. HOWEVER he said that in order to reserve, he needed my credit card number (over the phone). I said I didn't feel comfortable giving that. He told me to call 311 to find out if they are accredited or not. He said that he gets 90% of his business from 311 referrals. Then he said \"you must call me back in 10 minutes or I close my appointments for the night\". So I called 311. They said that there is no accredited test facility with the name \"total health & wellness\" . So I took a pass on this. Seems a little fishy. Be warned.",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUNtX091T09nEAE!2m1!1s0x0:0x3dd458fd0b92ee0e!3m1!1s2@1:CIHM0ogKEICAgICm_OuOOg%7C%7C?hl=en",
          "date": "4 years ago",
          "date_iso8601": "2021-12-22T04:59:21+00:00"
        },
        {
          "username": "apthc Sny22",
          "rating": 5,
          "contributor_id": "108980351654813375241",
          "user_review_count": 1,
          "user_photo_count": 0,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI7eTnUBpS_k6UbYEHyrdMv6GWwOdAWY7oyG0odB_incQS9Nw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100",
          "description": "I've been there 3 times in the past year to this urgent care center. Each time I've had great service. Everyone is very nice and professional, unlike many other places that I have been to here in New York City.  This is the closest urgent care near me and many times I am seen through their online urgent care as well. This place is amazing, and they are always their when my family and I need them.",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUNodnNhQVZBEAE!2m1!1s0x0:0x3dd458fd0b92ee0e!3m1!1s2@1:CIHM0ogKEICAgIChvsaAVA%7C%7C?hl=en",
          "date": "3 years ago",
          "date_iso8601": "2023-02-14T04:29:09+00:00"
        },
        {
          "username": "Rowaida Nicole Ballan",
          "rating": 4,
          "contributor_id": "101195196742824202722",
          "user_review_count": 54,
          "user_photo_count": 18,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKdzPVYe_vDrYMcZy04aZjNi861SdIDDDfF43GEN2j0xNgRAA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100",
          "description": "I needed an out of hours (after 8pm) urgent RT-PCR test for travel and wasn't having any luck with the places I googled. Total Health and Wellness came up in my search. To be honest, I thought it was a little dodgy but I was desperate so took the risk. Gave them my full credit card details over the phone, and I was then sent to some random building on 5th Ave at 9.45pm and told it would be closed and to call when I got there and I'd be let in. The doctor let us in and took my test in the hall of the building. Was told I'd have the results back in 1 hour (I paid $395). After a few follow up calls and messages my results were emailed to me around 12.30am. I admit I was nervous it was a scam but checked the CLIA ID (that came on the PCR results report) on the CDC website and it all came up legit. I was able to check in for my Emirates flight from JFK to DXB with no issues. My report was also accepted with no issues. The only reason for my 4 star review is that the report was emailed 2 hours later than I was initially told and when I was calling to follow up no one would answer at times.",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUNtX3Q2R1NnEAE!2m1!1s0x0:0x3dd458fd0b92ee0e!3m1!1s2@1:CIHM0ogKEICAgICm_t6GSg%7C%7C?hl=en",
          "date": "4 years ago",
          "date_iso8601": "2021-12-30T07:02:46+00:00"
        },
        {
          "username": "Mike Schubert",
          "rating": 1,
          "contributor_id": "111113796957315844173",
          "user_review_count": 45,
          "user_photo_count": 19,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWnMAT9memrlZlPL6RpljTAJThr7SXrNFTbMRq2GxhSHuRMoczh=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100",
          "description": "Tried to get a rapid test here and they told me to pay via Venmo and call my insurance to get it reimbursed. When I said I felt unsure about paying for a medical expense with Venmo and contacting my insurance after, the guy on the phone told me it\u2019s the 21st century and I should get used to it. Wild.",
